Q5
What is CapEx (Capital expenditure)?
ANS
SPENDING OF MONEY ON PHYSICAL INFRA UP FRONT AND DEDUCTED THAT EXPENSE FROM YOUR TAX BILL OVERTIME.

UP FRONT COST THAT HAS A VALUE THAT REDUCES OVERTIME.
Q6
What is OpEx (Operational expenditure)?
ANS
SPENDING MONEY ON SERVICES / PRODUCTS AND BEING BILLED FOR THEM CURRENTLY. YOU CAN DEDUCT IT FROM YOUR TAX BILL IN THE SAME YEAR.

THERE IS NO UPFRONT COST, YOU PAY FOR THE SERVICE OR PRODUCT AS YOU USE IT.
Q7
What is the benefit of using OpEx operational expenditure?
ANS
COMPANIES WANTING TO START A NEW BUSINESS OR GROW IT DO NOT HAVE TO INCUR UP FRONT COSTS TO TRY OUT A NEW PRODUCT OR SERVICE, INSTEAD THEY CAN GET INTO THE MARKET IMMEDIATELY AND PAY AS MUCH OR AS LITTLE FOR INFRA AS THE BUSINESS REQUIRES.

THEY CAN ALSO TERMINATE THAT COST IF AND WHEN THEY NEED TO DO SO.
Q8
What do we need if we build a data center?
ANS
ROUTERS, SWITCHES, FIREWALLS, SERVERS - CAPEX
Q9
What are some examples of OpEx operational expenditure?
ANS
PAY FOR MAINTENANCE SUCH AS LICENSES, SUBSCRIPTIONS, HEATING AND VENTILATION, AIR CONDITIONING, ELECTRICITY, TELEPHONE BILLS, HUMAN MANPOWER AND THEIR PAYROLL STUBS.
Q10
In cloud services all the CapEx and OpEx are available for a fraction of cost and the user pays as they use the services? True/False
ANS
TRUE - CAPEX REDUCTION, OPEX MODEL


